Note:
LOCKFILE - Reproducible-Build Dependency Pin Manifest (Tier 1)

Implements the lockfile substrate: a sorted, deterministic list of
exactly-resolved dependency versions with checksums. A lockfile is the
mechanism by which an arbitrary developer machine reproduces a
byte-identical build of a package. Mirrors Cargo.lock / package-lock.json
/ poetry.lock in role.

Determinism guarantee: lockfile_serialize emits entries in lexicographic
order by (name, version_string) so two correctly-implemented serializers
produce identical output for the same input. This is the property
package managers test against to verify a clean install matches the
recorded lockfile.

Layout (LockEntry, 64 bytes):
  offset  0 : name         (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : version      (8 bytes, Version pointer)
  offset 16 : source_kind  (8 bytes, see DEP_* constants from dependency_spec)
  offset 24 : source_url   (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset 32 : checksum     (8 bytes, String pointer - SHA-256 or BLAKE3 hex)
  offset 40 : dependencies (8 bytes, List<String> pointer - names of transitive deps)
  offset 48 : checksum_alg (8 bytes, see ALG_* constants)
  offset 56 : _reserved    (8 bytes - reserved for future fields)

Layout (Lockfile, 32 bytes):
  offset  0 : format_version (8 bytes)
  offset  8 : root_manifest_name (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset 16 : root_manifest_version (8 bytes, Version pointer)
  offset 24 : entries     (8 bytes, List<LockEntry> pointer)

References:
  - Cargo.lock format ........ https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/guide/cargo-toml-vs-cargo-lock.html
  - SLSA reproducible builds . https://slsa.dev/spec/v1.0/levels
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/version_constraint.runa" as VC

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let LOCK_ENTRY_SIZE be 64
Let LOCKFILE_SIZE be 32

Let LOCKFILE_FORMAT_VERSION be 1

Let ALG_SHA256 be 1
Let ALG_BLAKE3 be 2
Let ALG_SHA512 be 3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LOCK ENTRY
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a single locked dependency entry. The version is an owned
Version pointer (released via entry_destroy_deep). The dependencies list
must already have been allocated by the caller.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 64 bytes and populate every slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on any null mandatory input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_create" takes name as Integer, version as Integer, source_kind as Integer, source_url as Integer, checksum as Integer, checksum_alg as Integer, dependencies as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If version is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If checksum is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If checksum_alg is less than ALG_SHA256:
        Return 0
    End If
    If checksum_alg is greater than ALG_SHA512:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let e be proc allocate from Layout with LOCK_ENTRY_SIZE
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 0, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 8, version
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 16, source_kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 24, source_url
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 32, checksum
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 40, dependencies
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 48, checksum_alg
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with e, 56, 0
    Return e
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the entry record without disturbing subordinate strings, version,
or transitive-dep list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_destroy" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with e
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the entry and every owned subordinate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Conditionally release each non-null subordinate, then free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) where d is the number of transitive deps. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Double-free protection is caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_destroy_deep" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let version be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 8
    If version is not equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep from VC with version
    End If
    Let source_url be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 24
    If source_url is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with source_url
    End If
    Let checksum be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 32
    If checksum is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with checksum
    End If
    Let deps be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 40
    If deps is not equal to 0:
        Let dn be proc list_length from List with deps
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than dn:
            Let s be proc list_get from List with deps, i
            If s is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with s
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with deps
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with e
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ENTRY ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Expose the entry name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_name" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the locked version.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_version" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the integrity hash. Callers verifying the hash must use a
constant-time comparator from the crypto module.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The hash is the package manager's tamper-detection signal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_checksum" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the hashing algorithm identifier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lock_entry_checksum_alg" takes e as Integer returns Integer:
    If e is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with e, 48
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LOCKFILE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an empty lockfile rooted at the given package name and version.
The entries list is allocated as empty; the caller adds entries via
lockfile_add_entry.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, populate root metadata, and create an empty entry
list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null mandatory inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_create" takes root_name as Integer, root_version as Integer returns Integer:
    If root_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If root_version is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lf be proc allocate from Layout with LOCKFILE_SIZE
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc list_create from List
    If entries is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with lf
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with lf, 0, LOCKFILE_FORMAT_VERSION
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with lf, 8, root_name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with lf, 16, root_version
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with lf, 24, entries
    Return lf
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the lockfile and its entries list header. Does not deep-free
entries.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Destroy the list, free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for the list cleanup. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_destroy" takes lf as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with entries
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with lf
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the lockfile and deep-free every entry.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate entries calling lock_entry_destroy_deep, then call
lockfile_destroy.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n * d) for n entries and average d transitive deps. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Double-free protection is caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_destroy_deep" takes lf as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        Let n be proc list_length from List with entries
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than n:
            Let e be proc list_get from List with entries, i
            If e is not equal to 0:
                proc lock_entry_destroy_deep with e
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return proc lockfile_destroy with lf
End Process

@Reasoning
Append an entry to the lockfile.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
List push the entry pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller is responsible for entry lifetime.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_add_entry" takes lf as Integer, entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_push from List with entries, entry
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the entries list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_entries" takes lf as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Find an entry by package name. Linear scan.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterate entries comparing names with string_equals.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n * |name|). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if no match.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_find_entry" takes lf as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be proc list_length from List with entries
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than n:
        Let e be proc list_get from List with entries, i
        If e is not equal to 0:
            Let en be proc lock_entry_name with e
            If en is not equal to 0:
                Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with en, name
                If eq is equal to 1:
                    Return e
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SERIALIZATION (DETERMINISTIC)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Serialize the lockfile to a deterministic text format. The output is
the Runa-native lockfile format: a header line, the root package line,
and one entry block per locked dependency in name-then-version
lexicographic order.

Deterministic ordering is the load-bearing property: two callers
serializing the same logical lockfile must produce byte-identical output
so package managers can detect drift via simple hash comparison.

Format:
  # Runa lockfile - format version 1
  # AUTO-GENERATED - DO NOT EDIT
  root.name = "<name>"
  root.version = "<version-string>"

  [[entry]]
  name = "<name>"
  version = "<version-string>"
  checksum_alg = "<sha256|blake3|sha512>"
  checksum = "<hex>"

The order is enforced by sorting entries by name then version. Entries
with identical (name, version) collapse to a single record (deduped).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Construct a stable sorted view of the entries by allocating a parallel
index list, performing an insertion sort with byte-wise (name, version)
comparison, then emitting via StringBuilder.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n^2) insertion sort over n entries; acceptable because n is
typically in the dozens to hundreds and the sort runs once per
serialize call. Space: O(n) for the index list plus the rendered text.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The serialized output is intended for storage; no untrusted input is
parsed here. The deterministic-output property is itself a security
property because it lets reviewers spot tampering via diff.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lockfile_serialize" takes lf as Integer returns Integer:
    If lf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 24
    Let root_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 8
    Let root_version be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lf, 16

    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "# Runa lockfile - format version "
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, LOCKFILE_FORMAT_VERSION
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "# AUTO-GENERATED - DO NOT EDIT"
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "root.name = \""
    If root_name is not equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, root_name
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "root.version = \""
    If root_version is not equal to 0:
        Let rv_str be proc version_to_string from VC with root_version
        If rv_str is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, rv_str
            proc deallocate from Layout with rv_str
        End If
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10

    Note: Build sorted index over entries.
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        Let n be proc list_length from List with entries
        Let order be proc list_create from List
        If order is equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
            Return 0
        End If
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than n:
            proc list_push from List with order, i
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Note: Insertion sort.
        Let p be 1
        While p is less than n:
            Let cur be proc list_get from List with order, p
            Let q be p minus 1
            Let inserted be 0
            While inserted is equal to 0:
                If q is less than 0:
                    Set inserted to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let q_idx be proc list_get from List with order, q
                    Let cmp be proc compare_entries with entries, cur, q_idx
                    If cmp is less than 0:
                        Let q_val be proc list_get from List with order, q
                        proc list_set from List with order, q plus 1, q_val
                        Set q to q minus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set inserted to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            proc list_set from List with order, q plus 1, cur
            Set p to p plus 1
        End While

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than n:
            Let idx be proc list_get from List with order, j
            Let entry be proc list_get from List with entries, idx
            If entry is not equal to 0:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "[[entry]]"
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                Let en_name be proc lock_entry_name with entry
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "name = \""
                If en_name is not equal to 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, en_name
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10

                Let en_ver be proc lock_entry_version with entry
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "version = \""
                If en_ver is not equal to 0:
                    Let ev_str be proc version_to_string from VC with en_ver
                    If ev_str is not equal to 0:
                        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, ev_str
                        proc deallocate from Layout with ev_str
                    End If
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10

                Let alg_id be proc lock_entry_checksum_alg with entry
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "checksum_alg = \""
                If alg_id is equal to ALG_SHA256:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "sha256"
                End If
                If alg_id is equal to ALG_BLAKE3:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "blake3"
                End If
                If alg_id is equal to ALG_SHA512:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "sha512"
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10

                Let cs be proc lock_entry_checksum with entry
                proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "checksum = \""
                If cs is not equal to 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, cs
                End If
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with order
    End If

    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: total order on entries by (name, version). Used by the sort in
lockfile_serialize.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare names byte-wise via string_compare; on tie, compare versions
via version_compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name| + |version|) per call. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "compare_entries" takes entries as Integer, ai as Integer, bi as Integer returns Integer:
    Let a be proc list_get from List with entries, ai
    Let b be proc list_get from List with entries, bi
    If a is equal to 0:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let an be proc lock_entry_name with a
    Let bn be proc lock_entry_name with b
    Let nc be proc string_compare from StringCore with an, bn
    If nc is not equal to 0:
        Return nc
    End If
    Let av be proc lock_entry_version with a
    Let bv be proc lock_entry_version with b
    Return proc version_compare from VC with av, bv
End Process
